%N A393886 O.g.f. A(x) satisfies: [x^n] exp( n^8*x - n^6*A(x) ) = 0 for n >= 1.
%H A393886 Paul D. Hanna, <a href="/A393886/b393886.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..201</a>
%e A393886 O.g.f.: A(x) = x + 288*x^2 + 43670016*x^3 + 141728648527872*x^4 + 3896328523317120000000*x^5 + 557765622837598672328295186432*x^6 + ...
%e A393886 ILLUSTRATION OF DEFINITION.
%e A393886 The table of coefficients of x^k/k! in exp( n^8*x - n^6*A(x) ) begins
%e A393886   n = 1: [1,      0,         -576,        -262020096, ...];
%e A393886   n = 2: [1,    192,            0,      -16783441920, ...];
%e A393886   n = 3: [1,   5832,     33592320,                 0, ...];
%e A393886   n = 4: [1,  61440,   3772514304,   230420134232064, 0, ...];
%e A393886   n = 5: [1, 375000, 140616000000, 52720155936000000, 19708507778802048000000, 0, ...]; ...
%e A393886 in which a diagonal, the coefficient of x^n in row n, is all zeros.
%e A393886 RELATED SERIES.
%e A393886 exp(A(x)) = 1 + x + 577*x^2/2! + 262021825*x^3/3! + 3401488613748097*x^4/4! + 467559439807004084280961*x^5/5! + 401591251248457707293941758697921*x^6/6! + ...
%e A393886 where [x^n] exp(n^8*x) / exp(A(x))^(n^6) = 0 for n >= 1.
%o A393886 (PARI) {a(n,p=8,q=6) = my(A=[0], m); for(i=1, n+1, m=#A; A=concat(A, 0); A[m+1] = Vec( exp(m^p*x - m^q*Ser(A)) )[m+1]/(m^q) ); polcoef( Ser(A), n)}
%o A393886 for(n=1, 15, print1(a(n,8,6), ", "))
%Y A393886 Below, sequences with the parameters (p,q) indicated have an o.g.f. F(x) satisfying [x^n] exp( n^p*x - n^q*F(x) ) = 0 for n >= 1.
